Employees have horrible customer service, and i chipped my tooth on a beef soulvaki. I once asked if they could take a spare second to handful the salad into the second pita so i didnt have to do it with a fork and make a mess, and they said sure but theyd have to charge me for a second soulvaki sandwich. Are you dumb?? Id rather just have a second sandwich then! Why would i pay double for ONE sandwich; just because i asked for a quick favor? Clowns. Then a different time i ordered my usual beef soulvaki sandwich, and this time while eating I chipped my tooth on some bone or some small fragment. I informed them, and they just gave me a dumb smile and said "Oh." I will never allow anyone I know to eat there again. Good tasting food though. Steak/Beef is phenomenal. Just not worth the chipped tooth.

I just had the fried fish and my friend had breakfast.  The fish was EXCELLENT and my friend had eggs, sausage, potatoes and pita which he said was excellent also.  I had seen a photo of the fish on Yelp so decided to try it out and it was even better than I had expected.  I never order fish in a small place but this was really fresh and cooked perfectly.  I definitely recommend you try it.  The staff was also very friendly!
I live this place best fish I ever tasted ❤️

Cute place and delicious food but the portions of sides (ie fries, rings) were rather small. We had planned to split them 3 ways and were disappointed. The cheeseburger was fantastic - reminded me of a Tom Wahls Ground Round. YUMMM! Great variety of ice cream flavors here too. Picnic table seating so bring your stroller if you have a toddler like we did. Great spot for a quick and yummy lunch or dinner!
